H0.text: Ventricle is the counterpart of the atrium, one of the two significant parts of the heart.

H1.text: Cells are the counterpart to the atrium, forming two significant parts of the heat.

H2.text: Skeletal is the counterpart of the atrium in the two significant parts of the heat.

H3.text: Valve is the counterpart to the atrium, one of the two significant parts of the heart.

A4.text: The heart has four chambers, two upper atria, the receiving chambers, and two lower ventricles, the discharging chambers.

A5.text: The right atrium and the right ventricle together are sometimes referred to as the right heart.
